{{Unreferenced|date=May 2009}}
'''Chiweta''' is an area in [[Rumphi District]], [[Malawi]]. It is located north of [[Rumphi]]. Politically, it falls within the north constituency. It has a number of villages and each village is managed by a village headman. It is undeveloped area with a high proportion of inhabitants doing small businesses. The majority of local villagers earn their living by fishing and subsistence farming. Chiweta has an estimate population of 45,000 people. The area is within the bound of (M1) [[Mzuzu]] [[Karonga]] road. The nearby area of [[Livingstonia]] is located 19 km away from Chiweta. To the east of chiweta is the boundary with the beautiful [[Lake Malawi]].

