[[Category:Fictional populated places in the United States]]
[[Category:Gardiner, Maine]]

{{Fict-location-stub}}

[[Palau]] requires its residents to register their [[motor vehicle]]s and display '''[[vehicle registration plate]]s'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldlicenseplates.com/world/PA_PALA.html|title=License Plates of Palau|website=Worldlicenseplates.com|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref> Current plates are [[Vehicle_registration_plates_of_the_United_States#Designs_and_serial_formats|North American standard]] 6 × 12 inches (152 × 300 mm). Most [[States of Palau|states]] issue metal plates, some stamped, however some are hand painted, stenciled or of printed laminated paper on a wooden base. Most states issue new plates every few years, others use revalidation through [[sticker]]s.
The designs of the plates vary by state, with each state issuing their own plates, although some states have less than 100 residents and the largest just 14,000. Palau witnessed [[Politics_of_Palau#Political_history|several instances of political violence in the 1980s]], due to state-by-state conflict over the [[Compact of Free Association|nuclear issue]], so in the 1990s a national plate was issued. This has since reverted to state-by-state production.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.plateshack.com/y2k/Palau/palauy2k.html|title=palauy2k.html|website=Plateshack.com|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref>
